## Reusable Drafting Engine — Dish N Dash Legal Agent

This file is the reusable clause engine for the Dish N Dash Legal Agent.

It is not a random bank of legal snippets.  
It is not a copy-paste clause dump.  
It is not a generic template file.

It is the structured drafting library the system uses to:
- create contract language
- revise third-party paper
- strengthen weak clauses
- negotiate fallback positions
- preserve drafting consistency across agreements
- keep clause logic aligned with Dish N Dash’s business model, risk posture, and escalation rules

This library exists to give the legal agent reusable, high-quality, modular drafting language for creating and revising contracts while preserving:
- consistency
- precision
- negotiating flexibility
- operational realism
- clause-to-clause harmony
- escalation safety

The clause library is an execution asset. It is not free-floating text. Every clause in this file must be selected, adapted, and validated in context.

---

## Why a Clause Library Matters

A strong clause library matters because it prevents the most common drafting failures in startup legal work:

- ad hoc drafting under time pressure
- inconsistent positions across agreements
- weak fallback language when strong language gets rejected
- generic boilerplate that does not fit the business model
- revisions that solve one issue but create another
- repeated renegotiation of already-solved legal positions
- slow redrafting because every issue starts from zero
- hidden drift in defined terms, payment logic, liability structure, or IP posture

For Dish N Dash, this matters even more because the company operates across multiple legal-commercial surfaces at once:
- restaurant onboarding
- platform and marketplace-style terms
- reservations and pre-ordering flows
- loyalty and rewards logic
- vendor and SaaS relationships
- data-sensitive workflows
- payment-sensitive workflows
- analytics, branding, and content rights
- partnership and integration agreements
- internal governance and future financing preparation

A disciplined clause library preserves legal memory, speeds up revision, improves negotiation readiness, and reduces reliance on generic templates that do not fit how Dish N Dash actually operates.

